text=(:title Research Interests:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a[[#AASE]]%0a%0a! Research Publications%0a%0a[[#RPS]]%0a%0a* '''A Security Risk Assessment for Business Processes Deployment in the Cloud'''. Elio Goettelmann, Karim Dahman, Benjamin Gateau, Eric Dubois and Claude Godart. In SCC 2014 - The 11th International Conference on Services Computing, Alaska, USA (2014).%0a%0a* '''A Broker Framework for Secure and Cost-Effective Business Process Deployment on Multiple Clouds'''. Elio Goettelmann, Karim Dahman, Benjamin Gateau and Claude Godart. In CAiSE Forum 2014 - 26th International Conference on Advanced Information Systems Engineering, Thessaloniki, Greece (2014).%0a%0a* '''Alignement des Architectures SOA et des Procédures d'Entreprise : Une Approche Dirigée par les Modèles'''. Karim Dahman. Presses Académiques Francophones, 978-3-8416-2189-4 (2013).%0a%0a* '''Alignment and Change Propagation between Business Processes and Service-Oriented Architectures'''. Karim Dahman, François Charoy, Claude Godart. In SCC 2013 - The 10th International Conference on Services Computing, CA, USA (2013).%0a%0a* '''Governance and Analysis of Business Processes Change Impact on Service Oriented Architectures: A Model-Driven Approach''' - Gouvernance et étude de l'impact du changement des processus métiers sur les architectures orientées services : une approche dirigée par les modèles. Karim Dahman. Ph.D. Thesis, SCORE-UdL-INRIA Lorraine-LORIA, Nancy, France, (2012). [[http://tel.archives-ouvertes.fr/tel-00785771|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] (Abstract [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/these_resume.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] and Presentation [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/Presentation.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]])%0a%0a* '''Experimenting Crisis Response Coordination'''. Jörn Franke, Karim Dahman and Francois Charoy. In CSCW Workshop 2012 - The 2012 ACM Conference on Computer Supported Cooperative Work, Seattle, Washington, USA (2012).%0a%0a* '''Towards Consistency Management for a Business-Driven Development of SOA'''. Karim Dahman, François Charoy, Claude Godart. In EDOC 2011 - The 15th IEEE International Enterprise Distributed Object Computing Conference, Helsinki, Finland (2011). [[http://hal.inria.fr/inria-00597067/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a* '''From Business Process to Component Architecture: Engineering Business to IT Alignment'''. Karim Dahman, François Charoy, Claude Godart. In EDOCW 2011 - The 15th IEEE International Enterprise Distributed Object Computing Conference Workshops, Helsinki, Finland (2011). [[http://hal.inria.fr/inria-00597070/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a* '''Change Propagation in Decentralized Composite Web Services'''. Walid Fdhila, Aymen Baouab, Karim Dahman, Claude Godart, Olivier Perrin and François Charoy. In CollaborateCom 2011 - The 7th International Conference on Collaborative Computing, Orlando, Florida, USA (2011). [[http://hal.inria.fr/hal-00647004/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a* '''Generation of Component Based Architecture from Business Processes: Model Driven Engineering for SOA'''. Karim Dahman, François Charoy, Claude Godart. In ECOWS 2010 - The 8th IEEE European Conference on Web Services, Ayia Napa, Greece (2010). [[http://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/inria-00527476/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] (Poster [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/Poster.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] )%0a%0a%0a[[#RPE]]%0a%0a%0a[[#AASE]]%0a%0a! Technical Reports%0a%0a[[#RPS]]%0a%0a* '''Bridging the Gap between the Business Processes and the Service Oriented Architecture'''. Karim Dahman. Technical report, SCORE-INRIA Lorraine-LORIA-UHP, France, 2011. [[http://hal.inria.fr/inria-00608230/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a* '''Morphflow : Une approche générique basée sur les opérations pour la gestion du changement dynamique dans les Workflows flexibles'''. Karim Dahman. Master Thesis, ECOO-INRIA Lorraine-LORIA-INPL, France, 2008. [[http://hal.inria.fr/inria-00336534/en/|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a* '''Conception d’un prototype de générateur d’intergiciels temps réel embarqués dans l’automobile'''. Karim Dahman. Master Thesis, TRIO-INRIA Lorraine-LORIA-ISI, France, 2007. [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/Memoire_Dahman_Karim_2007.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]%0a%0a[[#RPE]]%0a%0a! Current Research Interests%0a%0a%0aCurrently, I'm interested in '''security risk assessment''' models for deploying business%0aprocesses on '''multiple Cloud environments''' while reducing functioning costs.%0a%0aSince the complexity of risk assessments is greatly increased%0awhen data is spread on multiple Cloud environments, then managing risks on information systems%0ais essential to guarantee their security. As a consequence, two important questions arise when '''outsourcing processes''' in Cloud environments. How to compare different Cloud offers when considering security? How to align process requirements with%0aexisting Cloud offers? To answer these questions, I focus on assessing security risks when distributing business process automations across multiple Cloud offers.%0a%0aI aim at offering the full power of '''Cloud Computing''' to composite applications developers while%0ashielding them from the complexity related to security risk%0aassessments in the Cloud. I also want to give them the capability to automatically generate secure and cost-effective applications across multiple clouds. %0a%0a%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a! Postdoctoral Research Areas%0a%0a%0aIn the [[http://score.loria.fr/|SCORE]] Research Team, I focused on the evolution patterns of the (human and automated) business processes and their impact on the enterprise information systems that support cross-domain workflow sharing. Those systems are seamlessly integrated to computer-based applications used to manage internal and external resources, including tangible assets, financial resources, materials, and human resources covering all the functions and processes of an enterprise/institution. In particular, I am interested in the '''Business Process Management (BPM)''', the '''Service Oriented Software Engineering (SOSE)''', and the '''Component Based Development (CBD)''' for an end-to-end development approach in the context of sustainable organization-specific virtual architectures and extended networks of the connected enterprises, namely the '''Service Oriented Computing (SOC) and Cloud Computing''' architectural foundations of the '''Message Oriented Architecture (MOA)''' and the '''Enterprise Service Bus (ESB)'''. %0a%0a%0aFor my Postdoctoral research I studied the Service-Component Based Architectural Change Impact for Cloud Oriented Adaptive Deployment (Apache Nuvem, OW2 FraSCAti).%0a%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a! PhD Research Topics%0a%0a%0aWith the BPM-SOSE-CBD interplay, the business architects are able to build/optimize cross-organizational solutions directly by creating/changing the business processes. In turn, the system architects are able to construct/adapt the '''Software as a Service (SaaS)''' ecosystems that are organized in a '''Service Oriented Architecture (SOA)''', and convey to the IT developers with a precise Business-IT understanding of the system implementation requirements. Moreover, this enables inexpensive systems adaptation to fit the (ever) evolving business conditions without altering the Business-IT alignment and the business value.%0a%0aFor my Ph.D. research (find my Ph.D. Thesis [[http://tel.archives-ouvertes.fr/tel-00785771|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] and Presentation [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/Presentation.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]] and Abstract [[http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/pdf/these_resume.pdf|http://www.loria.fr/~dahman/img/pdf.gif]]), the research areas were: %0a* Service Oriented Architectures (change) governance%0a* The relations between the Business Process Management and the Service Oriented Software Engineering%0a* Alignment between the business-driven architectures and the service-oriented infrastructures%0a* '''Model Driven Engineering (MDE)''' approaches for Software as a Service development%0a* Provisioning component-based architectures that support the Cloud Computing architectural paradigms and the Service Oriented Computing principles%0a* Business process optimizations, Service Oriented Architectures adaptations and Component-Based Architectures reconfigurations %0a%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a! Academic Areas of Specialization%0a%0a[[#AASS]]%0a%0aIn global, I'm also interested in :%0a* Business Process Management and '''Business Process Re-engineering (BPR)'''%0a* Inter-organizational workflows, i.e., (Human and automated) workflows such as trade procedures crossing organizational boundaries%0a* Business Process Agility and Virtual Enterprise Architecture Change Management%0a* Business-IT Alignment and IT capabilities Governance %0a* IT Flexibility and Adaptive Component-Based Architectures%0a* Task-centric Business Service Design and '''Process Change-Aware Information Systems'''%0a* (Incremental) Model Driven Engineering and Model Change Impact Analysis%0a* Round-Tripping between IT and Business Process%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a%0a%25right%25''"Computers are useless. They can only give you answers"'' - Pablo Picasso
