diff:1331722415:1315814496:=3,9c3,9%0a%3c In the [[http://score.loria.fr/|SCORE]] Research Team, I focus on the evolution patterns of the (human and automated) business processes and their impact on the enterprise information systems that support cross-domain workflow sharing. Those systems are seamlessly integrated to computer-based applications used to manage internal and external resources, including tangible assets, financial resources, materials, and human resources covering all the functions and processes of an enterprise/institution. In particular, I'm interested in the '''Business Process Management (BPM)''', the '''Service Oriented Software Engineering (SOSE)''', and the '''Component Based Development (CBD)''' for an end-to-end developement approach in the context of an organization-specific virtual architecture or an extended network of connected enterprises, namely the '''Service Oriented Computing (SOC) and Cloud Computing''' architectural foundations of the '''Message Oriented Architecture (MOA) and Enterprise Service bus (ESB)'''. %0a%3c %0a%3c With the BPM-SOSE-CBD interplay, the business architects are able to build/optimize cross-organizational solutions directly by creating/changing the business processes. In turn, the system architects are able to construct/adapt the Software as a Service (SaaS) architectures that are organized in a '''Service Oriented Architecture (SOA)''', and convey to the IT developers with a precise Business-IT understanding of the system implementation requirements. Moreover, this enables inexpensive systems adaptation to fit the (ever) evolving business conditions without altering the Business-IT alignment and the business value.%0a%3c %0a%3c For my Ph.D. research, the topics I'm currently interested in: %0a%3c * Service Oriented Architectures (change) governance%0a%3c * The relations between the Business Process Management and the Service Oriented Software Engineering%0a---%0a> In the [[http://score.loria.fr/|SCORE]] Research Team, I focus on the evolution patterns of the business processes and their impact in the enterprise information systems that support the business cross-domain sharing. Those systems are seamlessly integrated computer-based applications used to manage internal and external resources, including tangible assets, financial resources, materials, and human resources covering all the functions and processes of an enterprise/institution. In particular, I'm interested in the '''Business Process Management (BPM)''', the '''Service Oriented Software Engineering (SOSE)''', and the '''Component Based Development (CBD)''' for an end-to-end developement approach in the context of an organization-specific architecture or an extended network of connected enterprises, namely the '''Service Oriented Computing (SOC)''' architectural foundations. %0a> %0a> With the BPM-SOSE-CBD interplay, the business architects are able to build/optimize cross-organizational solutions directly by creating/changing the business processes. In turn, the system architects are able to construct/adapt the software system architectures that are organized in a '''Service Oriented Architecture (SOA)''', and convey to the IT developers with a precise Business-IT understanding of the system implementation requirements. Moreover, this enables inexpensive systems adaptation to fit the (ever) evolving business conditions without altering the Business-IT alignment and the business value.%0a> %0a> For my Ph.D. research, the topics I'm currently interested in are: %0a> * SOA (change) governance%0a> * The relations between the BPM and the SOSE%0a11,14c11,15%0a%3c * '''Model Driven Engineering''' approaches for Software as a Service developement%0a%3c * Provisioning component-based architectures that support the Cloud Computing architectural paradigms and the Service Oriented Computing principles%0a%3c * Business process optimizations, Service Oriented Architectures adaptations and Component-Based Architectures reco