diff:1308172506:1308169230:=3,13c3,13%0a%3c In the [[http://score.loria.fr/|SCORE]] Research Team, I focus on the evolution patterns of the business processes and their impact in the enterprise information systems that support the business cross-domain sharing. Those systems are seamlessly integrated computer-based applications used to manage internal and external resources, including tangible assets, financial resources, materials, and human resources covering all the functions and processes of an enterprise/institution. In particular, I'm interested in the Business Process Management (BPM), the Service Oriented Software Engineering (SOSE), and the Component Based Development (CBD) for an end-to-end developement approach in the context of an organization-specific architecture or an extended network of connected enterprises, namely the Service Oriented Computing (SOC) architectural foundations. %0a%3c %0a%3c With the BPM-SOSE-CBD interplay, the business architects are able to build/optimize cross-organizational solutions directly by creating/changing the business processes. In turn, the system architects are able to construct/adapt the software system architectures, and convey to the IT developers with a precise Business-IT understanding of the system implementation requirements. Moreover, this enables inexpensive systems adaptation to fit the (ever) evolving business conditions without altering the Business-IT alignment and the business value.%0a%3c %0a%3c For my Ph.D. research, the topics I'm currently interested in are: %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c * Service-Oriented Architectures (SOA) Governance%0a%3c * The relations between the Business Process Management and the Service Oriented Software Engineering%0a%3c * Alignement between the business-driven architectures and the service-oriented infrastructures%0a%3c * Model Driven Engineering approach for the software solution developement based on a SOA%0a---%0a> In the [[http://score.loria.fr/|SCORE]] Research Team, I focus o